725328f-a.title: Queens: 41st Avenue - Main Street
725328f-a.text:
(1)
10-14 Forty-first Ave., north side, east of Main Street, showing
the Wright property from 1873 to 1898. Eugene L. Armbruster states
that in 1837 the Wright house stood on the north side of Madison Street
(now Forty-first Ave.) at the corner of Main Street . However, in
1893, the two buildings at the corner were owned by C.H. Hurst while
the next two were owned by W. Wright.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MA BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, showing a rear view.
1922.
Eugene L. Armoruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

727321f-a.title: Queens: Main Street - 41st Avenue
727321f-a.text:
Eain Street at Forty-first Avenue, showing two views looking
eastward from the Main Street elevated station of the Long Island
Railroad. At the left of the station in hoth views are the re-
mains of the Flushing Institute. The spire at the right back-
ground of both views is that of St. Michael's R.C. Church. The
peaked roof house in vi-w No. 2 beyond the awning and shade sign
is the Wright house on Forty-first Avenue.
February 24, 1925.
Views 1 arnd 2
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

727322f-b.title: Queens: Main Street - 41st Avenue
727322f-b.text:
Eia Street., west side, between Forty-first Ave. and Forty-first
Road, Ehawing - gas station on lot 57 which was once the station and
depot of Oliver Charlicks' Railroad,(popularly called ''The White Line',)
because of the white cars that were usedl This is a set of two views.
This building is not in existence in 1926.
1922.
View 2: March 1924.
Eumene L. Armbruster Collection.
